Validation allows additional properties if "additionalProperties" is set to False in the schema. Instead, the validator should raise an exception. The JSON Schema validation specification, [section 5.4.4.4](http://json-schema.org/latest/json-schema-validation.html#anchor68) contains the rules on how to handle "additionalProperties".


```python
from flex.core import validate
schema = {
  'type': 'object',
  'additionalProperties': False,
  'properties': {
    'name': {
      'type': 'string',
      'minLength': 3,
    },
  }
}
data = {
  'wrong': 10,
}
validate(schema, data)
```

