Hi, 

I have found that if clause in Block.forward() is executed in main thread and causes delay if outputs of former operators are related. 

For example:

```
// pseudo code
class DemoBlock(Block):
    def __init__(self, **kwargs):
        super(DemoBlock, self).__init__(**kwargs)
        self.fc = nn.Dense(10)
    def forward(self, x):
        x = self.fc(x)
        if x.sum() > 0:
            return x
        else:
            return x+1
```

